\f0\b \cf0 w, x, y, z
\f1\b0  - the B-format signals. \

\f0\b angle
\f1\b0  - the angle of distortion in radians, from -pi to pi. 0 reduces the directivity to the w component only, bringing everything to the middle of the image. Values greater then pi/2 increase the gain of x, y, z while reducing w; this range of values can be used to exaggerate the directional impression. Values between pi/2 and -pi/2 bring the image from unchanged, through the center, to inverted directional components. The default, pi/2, results in no change.\
